11/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos kicks off a three-day visit to neighbouring Bulgaria on Monday (11 October). 
He will meet with Bulgarian counterpart Georgi Parvanov, Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and the Bulgarian Orthodox Church's Patriarch Maxim. 
A bilateral business forum will be held during his stay as well. 
(ANA, VOA, bTV - 11/10/04)
